   The Rangers' potent lineup whiffed on the potential breakthrough
and doomed the American League West champions to a 3-1 loss
Thursday night at Yankee Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Second baseman Mark McLemore, shortstop Royce Clayton and left
fielder Rusty Greer failed to produce with runners aboard second
and third during the critical fifth inning.
</P>
