Stevens. Despite no outs, neither crossed the plate.
</P>
<P>
   McLemore, who hit .163 this season against left-handers, stepped
into the batter's box hitting right-handed against Yankees
left-hander Andy Pettitte. Yankees manager Joe Torre played third
baseman Scott Brosius and shortstop Derek Jeter at normal depth and
pulled in the right side of his infield.
</P>
