<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ADAIR-GLARE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VICTIM`S MOTHER BANNED FROM MURDER TRIAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY PHILLIP W. BROWNE  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- The mother of murder victim Robert Adair was
barred from the San Fernando courthouse after an alleged
confrontation in a restroom with her former daughter-in-law, Jeanie
Adair, accused of the crime.
</P>
<P>
   Superior Court Judge L. Jeffery Wiatt ordered Margarita
Sutcliffe to stay at least 500 yards away from the courthouse while
Adair, who is free on $250,000 bail, is on trial.
</P>
<P>
   After the hearing, Sutcliffe insisted she ``never said a thing''
in the restroom to the 39-year-old Adair, who is accused of killing
her husband with a baseball bat to collect insurance. Adair told
her attorney Thursday that Sutcliffe said, ``You're going to
burn.'' The lawyer alerted the judge.
</P>
<P>
   ``She is a liar,'' Sutcliffe said. ``All she did was walk in,
look at her hair and leave. I didn't say anything. Jeanie may
escape justice in court if they find her innocent, but she will not
escape God's justice. That's what I believe in.''
</P>
<P>
   Adair's attorney, Richard Plotin, declined to comment, as did
Adair.
</P>
<P>
   Adair's defense case began with Plotin's questioning Los Angeles
Police Department Detective Patricia Ferguson about why she did not
pursue a case against Mindy Shapiro. ``There was no reason ...
because Mindy was not involved in the murder of Robert Adair,''
Ferguson said.
</P>
<P>
   Jeanie Adair claims Shapiro orchestrated an attack as an act of
revenge because she was having an affair with Shapiro's former
husband.
</P>
<P>
   Plotin also asked Ferguson why she did not pursue cases against
two convicted felons identified early as possible suspects.
</P>
<P>
   ``There were extensive interviews, and our investigation
revealed they were not connected,'' Ferguson said. ``Even the
physical description Jeanie Adair gave of her attackers did not
fit. She described one suspect as having a belly. Neither of them
had bellies.''
</P>
<P>
   Under cross-examination by prosecutor Marsh Goldstein, Ferguson
discounted the theory that the two stole $250 from the Adair home,
killed Robert Adair and left Jeanie Adair alive.
</P>
<P>
   ``They left Jeanie alive, an eyewitness, and that does not make
sense,'' Ferguson said, noting that one of the two would go to
prison for life under California's ``three strikes, you're out''
law if convicted of another ``strike.''
</P>
<P>
   She said the two also were at a pawn shop soon after the time of
the murder. She called it unlikely they would have been trying to
pawn a black-and-white television if they had just stolen $250.
</P>
<P>
   ``Also, the third striker would have immediately left the area
if he killed Robert, not go to a pawn shop. His actions just don't
fit.''
</P>
<P>
   Police say Adair killed her 40-year-old husband in 1996 and
tried to cover it up by injuring herself and claiming a
home-invasion robbery occurred. Goldstein has told the jury that
Adair killed her husband to get $400,000 in life insurance and end
their troubled marriage.
</P>
<P>
   But Plotin said Adair had no reason to covet her husband's
insurance because she was set to receive $275,000 settlement for an
on-the-job knee injury.
</P>
<P>
   Outside the courthouse, Plotin claimed LAPD detectives succumbed
to pressure from Sutcliffe and other relatives of Robert Adair to
arrest Jeanie Adair.
</P>
<P>
   ``They failed to thoroughly investigate the case. They didn't
even analyze the blood on Jeanie's clothing,'' Plotin said, noting
that recent test results revealed there wasn't a drop of her
husband's blood on her clothing.
</P>
<P>
   Adair could go to prison for life with no chance of parole if
she is convicted of murder with the special circumstances of lying
in wait and killing for financial gain.
</P>
<P>
   The trial is expected to continue today with testimony from
another detective and cable company witnesses who reportedly heard
a struggle in Adair's condominium, located in suburban Sylmar.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
