surprised Swedes as much as anybody else, this largely
unreconstructed welfare state is suddenly one of Europe's most
vibrant economies. And after nearly three decades of sluggishness
in which the output per person slumped from third highest in the
world to 18th, just behind Italy, the Swedish economy is in the
midst of a powerful transformation. By Edmund L. Andrews.
