</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-ORISA _ He came to Atlanta as a Catholic priest in the
Capuchin order of Franciscans, and served a parish here. Earlier
this month, he was ordained again, as a priest in Orisa, an
African-based religion that emphasizes ancestor worship. We attend
an Orisa service and talk to other African-Americans who have been
attracted to the religions they say were those of their ancestors.
(White, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   DEPRESSION _ Clinical depression can cause severe aches and
pains, debilitating fatigue, chills and overheating, erratic sleep
patterns and difficulty concentrating. If you have those or other
depression symptoms, you might have been checked out for
mononucleosis, thyroid or blood sugar imbalances, chronic
infection, parasites, fibromyalgia, chronic fatigue syndrome and
heart or stomach diseases. Depression can mimic them all. Thursday
is National Depression Screening Day, an opportunity for anyone to
be checked out for depression without charge. (Lamb, Dayton Daily
News). 20. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHIZOPHRENIA _ The benefits of psychotherapy and social
support, long recognized in treating depressive disorders, also are
gaining acceptance as an essential element in treating
schizophrenia and other mental illnesses that involve psychoses.
``We know that people with severe mental illness need more than a
pill and a doctor's visit,'' says Laurie Flynn, executive director
of the National Alliance for the Mentally Ill (NAMI). (Dayton Daily
News). 22. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
