<P>
   COXNET SCIHEALTH 1005 -- Tissue plasminogen activator (TPA) has
been minimizing stroke damage by dissolving blood clots since 1996,
but it's still not widely known that people can spare themselves a
lifetime disability by hustling to the hospital when stroke
symptoms first appear (Lamb, Dayton Daily News) Art includes
3-column color illustration of a stroke victim undergoing therapy.
