<P>
   COXNET SCIHEALTH 1005 -- Tissue plasminogen activator (TPA) has
been minimizing stroke damage by dissolving blood clots since 1996,
but it's still not widely known that people can spare themselves a
lifetime disability by hustling to the hospital when stroke
symptoms first appear (Lamb, Dayton Daily News) Art includes
3-column color illustration of a stroke victim undergoing therapy.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TIPS BOX -- Symptoms to recognize when having a stroke.
WITH: HEALTH &AMP; MEDIA -- Books offer tips on dealing with eating
disorders. (Staff, Cox News Service) Art includes three 6-pica
color photos of book jackets and one 6-pica color illustration of a
computer
</P>
<P>
   WITH: PREVENTION -- Heavy backpacks are not good for children.
(Lore, Atlanta Journal Constitution) Art includes 18-pica color
photo of a child with a heavy backpack
</P>
<P>
   WITH: MEDICINE -- Facts about a new inhaler that helps reduce
the duration of bouts of influenza. (Staff, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: YOUR HEALTH -- Drug advertisers' objectives are simple:
Sell you products. (Lamb, Dayton Daily News)
