</P>
<P>
   ECONOMY (Undated) _ The number of workers on U.S. payrolls fell
by 8,000 in September, the first drop since January 1996, as
Hurricane Floyd caused flooding and shut businesses. While job
growth slowed, average hourly wages posted their biggest gain in
more than 10 years, rising 7 cents, to to $13.37. The jobless rate
remained at 4.2 percent, a 29-year low. The Dow was up 73 points at
2 p.m. 1,100 words. By Louis Uchitelle.
</P>
