   LAGARDE-LAWFIRM (Chicago) _ Christine Lagarde becomes the first
woman to lead Baker &AMP; McKenzie, one of the world's largest law
firms. Her election, by an overwhelming majority of the Chicago
firm's 548 partners on Thursday night, of whom 91 percent are men,
is a sign that women are finally moving into power at some major
law firms, which have been behind even their clients in corporate
America at promoting women into management's upper echelons. 1,800
words. By Melody Petersen.
</P>
