<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (category `i') &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PINOCHET-EXTRADITE (London) _ British judge rules that the
former Chilean leader Augusto Pinochet should be extradited to
Spain. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   With:
</P>
<P>
   PINOCHET-REACT CHILE (Santiago) _ Reaction in Chile to the
ruling. By Clifford Krauss.
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-ASSESS (New Delhi) _ News Analysis: Something amazing
happened in Indian politics in the elections that just concluded.
In the large southern state of Andhra Pradesh, the party that
promised the freebies lost. And the politician who warned there's
no free lunch won. The larger question for India now is whether the
winner's strategy for economic growth will catch on in other
states. By Celia W. Dugger.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-PRISONERS (Jerusalem) _ New snag in peace effort as
Israel misses deadline to release Palestinian prisoners. By Joel
Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   EMBASSY-BOMB-ARREST (Undated) _ Arrest of suspect in bombing of
U.S. Embassy in Tanzania to be announced in New York today. He's
the first arrested in Tanzanian bombing. Low level, but may lead to
bigger fish. By Benjamin Weiser. &QL;
</P>
