   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TREATY-GLANCE _ The main points of the treaty. (Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   HMO _ WASHINGTON _ Folo on House approval of managed health care
legislation. (Carr, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-SCAMS _ WASHINGTON _ New technologies are making it
easier for con artists to rip off would-be travelers. Many fraud
perpetrators who use the Internet to expand their pool of victims
are targeting older travelers. On Friday morning, the American
Society of Travel Agents will discuss the latest scams and provide
advice on how to avoid getting conned. (Geewax, Cox News Service).
18.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (t) travel categories.
</P>
<P>
   TAX-LOTTERY _ WASHINGTON _ Life for Gladys J. Cook was a gamble
that finally paid off big _ really, really big. Now the estate of
the $17 million Texas Lottery winner is being ordered by the
Internal Revenue Service to share more of the spoils _ to the tune
of an additional $1.04 million. (Moskal, Cox News Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   BIRM-MAYOR _ BIRMINGHAM _A runoff is expected, but Birmingham
voters will take a big step Tuesday (Oct. 12) toward picking a
successor to 20-year Mayor Richard Arrington. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
