<SLUG> BC-CARS-GLANCE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AT A GLANCE: 2000 FORD TAURUS SEDAN/WAGON
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   THE PACKAGE: Midsize, four-door, five- or six-passenger, V-6
powered, front-wheel-drive sedan or wagon.
</P>
<P>
   HIGHLIGHTS: Dumping the controversial space-age styling
introduced in 1996, Ford will roll out the new Taurus in December.
It is nice looking but not radical. Gone is the weird oval rear
window. There is more head room, and the base engine gets 10 more
horsepower.
</P>
<P>
   NEGATIVES: Side air bags are optional; they should be standard.
</P>
<P>
   MAJOR COMPETITORS: Toyota Camry, Honda Accord, Chevrolet Lumina,
Chevrolet Impala, Mazda 626, Buick Regal, Buick Century, Oldsmobile
Intrigue, Pontiac Grand Prix, Plymouth Breeze/Dodge
Stratus/Chrysler Cirrus, Hyundai Sonata, Mercury Sable (a clone of
the Taurus), Nissan Altima, Saturn L-series. EPA fuel economy: 20
miles per gallon city/28 highway (base 155-horsepower engine); 17
city/26 highway (optional 200-horsepower engine).
</P>
<P>
   BASE PRICE RANGE: No prices announced yet, but they are expected
to be close to last year's prices, which ranged from $17,560 to
$19,560.
</P>
<P>
   ON THE ROAD RATING: A-plus.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
