<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Saturday, Oct. 9 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
please contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News at (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   SURF-WEEKEND (Los Angeles) _ With triple-digit temperatures
inland and especially high surf generated by a storm off of New
Zealand, lifeguards from Venice to Malibu are bracing for a busy _
and dangerous _ weekend. County officials are scrambling to hire
more lifeguards for the weekend but are having difficulty because
it is off season. Six-foot sets are crashing onto beaches and
breaking surfboards. Waves are expected to reach eight to 10 feet
Saturday. By Michael Coit and Troy Anderson. (Will move in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   RELIGIOUS-ICON (Los Angeles) _ Thousands of worshipers are
expected to turn out at Our Lady of the Valley Catholic Church to
view a traveling image of the icon portraying Our Lady of
Guadalupe, the patron saint of Mexico. The image will be on view
today through Sunday and is one of 140 digital reproductions
blessed by Pope John Paul II, which depicts the image of the Virgin
Mary on a shawl dating from 1531. By Robert Monroe. (Will move in
the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BABYDOL-MADAM (Los Angeles) _ Another day in court in the case
against accused madam Jody Babydol Gibson. The judge already has
thrown out charges of conspiracy to pander. By Jesse Hiestand.
(Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CA-BUILD (Los Angeles) _ With highway construction starting to
flex its muscles and the Southern California region showing
substantial gains in all sectors, California's total construction
activity for the first eight months of 1999 is up 13.4 percent from
the corresponding period last year, totaling $33.5 billion,
according to statistics released Friday by Burbank-based
Construction Industry Research Board. By Gregory J. Wilcox. (Will
move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
