<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Oct. 9. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
CANYON (Phoenix) - An amendment that environmentalists say would
gut all noise restrictions on air tours over Grand Canyon National
Park passed the Senate this week. Ironically, the amendment was
sponsored by Arizona Sen. John McCain, who stakes his environmental
record on protecting Grand Canyon National Park and was the
architect of flight restrictions passed in 1987. The amendment, if
it becomes law, would eliminate recently proposed caps on the
number of air-tour flights over the canyon, eliminate the number of
aircraft that may fly over the park and eliminate a curfew on
flights during sunrise and sunset. By STEVE YOZWIAK. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
