<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, OCTOBER 9
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-NY-CHASE-JOBS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Oct. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent Thursday, Oct. 7,
about the decision by the Chase Manhattan Corporation to move 3,500
jobs out of New York City referred imprecisely to the portion of
the company's work force involved. The positions to be relocated
amount to 10 percent of Chase's work force in the New York
metropolitan area, not of its entire work force, which numbers
76,500 employees across the country.
</P>
<P>
   BC-LIMEY-FILM-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Thursday, Oct. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Oct. 7,
about ``The Limey,'' directed by Steven Soderbergh, with leading
actors including Terence Stamp, misidentified the actress with whom
he starred in the 1967 film ``Poor Cow.'' It was Carol White, not
Julie Christie.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CONTACT-THEATER-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Thursday, Oct. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Oct. 7,
about ``Contact,'' at Lincoln Center, misidentified the musical
film noir sequence that featured the line ``She came at me in
sections.'' It was from ``The Band Wagon,'' with Fred Astaire and
Cyd Charisse, not ``Singin' in the Rain.''
</P>
</TEXT>
