<HEADLINE>
SENDING A MONDAY MESSAGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Monday practices at Spaulding Field are usually
peaceful. UCLA players stretch sore muscles in routine drills and
the coaches correct mistakes in an easy, reassuring manner. There's
no tackling and little contact.
</P>
<P>
   But this week, Monday's practice included cracking helmets,
colliding shoulder pads and a 15-minute scrimmage _ the first
Monday scrimmage of Bob Toledo's coaching career.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted to turn up the heat,'' Toledo said. ``(The players)
know I'm not happy. I told them, `It's not punishment, it's to get
better.' . . . I want to see us get more physical.''
</P>
<P>
   Toledo was concerned about his team's psyche after a last-minute
loss to Arizona State eliminated the Bruins from the Rose Bowl
race. (UCLA has lost five of its last seven games, dating to last
year.) He hoped a scrimmage would sever any lingering lethargy and
prepare the Bruins for tonight's game against Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a really good week of practice,'' Toledo said Thursday.
``There was no complaining. They responded very well. I hope it
pays off.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Not ready: Don't expect former quarterback Drew Bennett to
get much playing time tonight at his new position, receiver.
Although Bennett understands the offense and has superb hands, he's
learning the footwork required to run precise pass routes.
</P>
<P>
   ``He understands where to go, but running routes takes a lot of
work,'' Toledo said. ``He needs a lot of work.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Getting his kicks? Oregon kicker Nathan Villegas is
questionable because of a torn anterior cruciate ligament in his
right (kicking) knee suffered two weeks ago against USC. One of the
Pac-10's best place-kickers, Villegas tore the ligament celebrating
a kick in overtime.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you watch the celebration, you can't figure out how or why
he got hurt,'' Ducks coach Mike Bellotti said. ``More amazing is
that doctors think he could join us'' and kick with a torn
ligament.
</P>
<P>
   If Villegas can't kick tonight, the Ducks will use senior Josh
Frankel, who has made 3 of 4 field goals.
</P>
<P>
   __ Hometown team: Offensive tackle Bryce Bohlander is one of
UCLA's best freshmen and its only Oregon native. He attended McNary
High in Keizer and picked UCLA over the Ducks.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's done a heck of a job for a freshman,'' offensive line
coach Mark Weber said. ``He needs to get more comfortable, but that
will come with experience. He's got such good knee bend and hip
movement. He really plays stronger than his (270 pounds).''
</P>
<P>
   __ Odds and ends: Kickoff is 7:24 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA will operate a free parking shuttle from the Parsons
Engineering Building in Pasadena to the Rose Bowl. Service begins
four hours before kickoff and ends one hour after the game. There
is a $4 parking charge for the Parsons lot.
</P>
<P>
   Kickoff for the Oct. 16 game against Cal is 12:30 p.m.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
