Christine Lagarde at the offices of Baker &AMP; McKenzie on Wednesday.
Lagarde became the first woman to lead the firm, one of the world's
largest, on Thursday after an election by the Chicago-based firm's
548 partners, of whom 91 percent are men. Lagarde's election is a
sign that women are finally moving into power at some major law
firms, which have been behind even their clients in corporate
America at promoting women into management's upper echelons. (Steve
Kagan/New York Times Photo) LITE
