<HEADLINE>
SPECIAL PLANS FOR ENGLISH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MISSOULA, Mont. _ Mark this down: If the Cal State Northridge
football team upsets Montana today, Kwasi English's first trip here
will be memorable.
</P>
<P>
   English, a reserve cornerback, promised Friday to scale the hill
behind Montana's Washington-Grizzly Stadium, up to where there is a
large ``M'' imprinted in white letters.
</P>
<P>
   English, a senior, might as well make the most of his second
road game this season. He didn't travel to CSUN's Big Sky
Conference opener at Eastern Washington on Sept. 25 but might have
earned this trip because of his fourth-quarter blocked punt against
Idaho State last week at home.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sweating right now,'' English said after practice Friday
night at Washington-Grizzly Stadium. ``I'm just trying to control
my adrenaline, so I can have some (today).''
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Kearin, CSUN's interim head coach, said English provides
depth in a secondary depleted by injuries to Hassan Abdul-Malik and
Dwan Vance. But English's special-teams ability is also a factor.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's proven he can block a kick,'' Kearin said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Decision time: Kearin has a decision to make today who will
return punts: Terrence Jones, who is averaging 9.5 yards per return
but has a bad hamstring, or Steve Forte, who hasn't returned one
this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Forte) is not as good at catching the ball,'' Kearin said.
``We'll mix it up.''
</P>
<P>
   Forte is CSUN's starting strong safety. He is third on the team
with 26 tackles.
</P>
<P>
   __ Making the call: Freshman wide receiver Greg Orlando, who
hasn't caught a pass this season, has a sore right wrist and might
redshirt. Orlando has broken the wrist three times.
</P>
<P>
   __ Weather report: It sprinkled at the end of CSUN's practice at
Washington-Grizzly Stadium on Friday night, but the forecast for
today is a high in the mid-60s and clear skies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
